              "content": "# PEMBERTON RFQ (S32-821314) — SPRINT STATUS\n\n## PHASE 1: ANALYSIS COMPLETE ✓\n- [x] Read full RFQ pack (invitation, MSA, GTCs, SLA, pricing, compliance, questionnaire)\n- [x] Identify walk-away issues (3) + high-priority items (5)\n- [x] Map battle of forms (GTCs override MSA on indemnity, liability, IP)\n- [x] Quantify worst-case indemnity exposure (unlimited, uninsurable)\n- [x] Draft top-3 redline strategy with fallback positions\n\n## PHASE 2: SPONSOR APPROVAL (IN PROGRESS)\n- [ ] Schedule 5-min call with commercial sponsor\n  - Use: EXEC-SUMMARY-1PAGE.md (1-pager) + REDLINE-STRATEGY-TOP-3.md (detailed)\n  - Key ask: Approval to proceed with all 3 redlines vs. pick-and-choose\n  - Key point: Indemnity cap is non-negotiable (insurance gate); others negotiable\n- [ ] Confirm sponsor walk-away thresholds:\n  - Termination: At what concurrent order volume do setup costs break even?\n  - Indemnity: Can insurance carrier quote on capped model? (If no → cannot bid)\n  - Benchmarking: What blended margin target drives ROI?\n- [ ] Get sponsor sign-off on fallback strategy (order of concessions)\n\n## PHASE 3: PRE-BID OUTREACH (IF CLARIFICATION WINDOW OPEN)\n- [ ] Identify bid clarification window dates (check invitation letter)\n- [ ] Draft email to Pemberton procurement:\n  - Subject: \"Redlined MSA for Alignment on Commercial Terms — Pemberton RFQ [ref]\"\n  - Attach: Marked-up MSA with 3 redlines + 1-page rationale per redline\n  - Frame: \"We're interested in this framework and want to flag these early.\"\n  - Tone: Business-neutral, not defensive\n- [ ] Send to Pemberton procurement contact (Priya Khatri, Senior Category Manager, Indirect MRO)\n- [ ] Set reminder to follow up if no response within 5 business days\n\n## PHASE 4: INSURANCE & PRICING\n- [ ] Call insurance carrier:\n  - Ask if they can quote on contractual indemnity capped at 12-month fees + claim control\n  - If yes: Get preliminary premium estimate; factor into bid\n  - If no: Escalate to sponsor as deal-blocker\n- [ ] Work with commercial/pricing team:\n  - Confirm blended margin target (if no redlines accepted, what price increase needed?)\n  - Validate breakeven concurrent order volume for setup cost absorption\n  - Model profit impact across 3 scenarios (all redlines / partial / none)\n\n## PHASE 5: FINAL BID SUBMISSION\n- [ ] Finalize redlined MSA based on sponsor feedback + any Pemberton pre-bid signals\n- [ ] Prepare one-page rationale for each redline (for bid response cover memo)\n- [ ] Confirm all 1,247 SKU ceiling prices in pricing schedule (check with commercial)\n- [ ] Draft RFP questionnaire response:\n  - Flag any questions asking bidder to commit to non-MSA terms\n  - Cross-check against redlined MSA to ensure consistency\n- [ ] Submit bid before deadline (hold 24h buffer for last-minute checks)\n\n## MATERIALS READY FOR SPONSOR CALL\n- ✓ REDLINE-STRATEGY-TOP-3.md (detailed 3-redline pitch + copy-paste language)\n- ✓ EXEC-SUMMARY-1PAGE.md (1-pager for quick reference)\n- [ ] Scenario financial model (3 outcomes: all redlines / partial / none) — to confirm\n- [ ] Fallback negotiation matrix (ideal / fallback 1 / walk-away) — already in REDLINE-STRATEGY\n\n## CRITICAL DECISION GATES\n1. **Indemnity cap (Insurance):** If carrier won't quote on capped model → cannot bid (drop out)\n2. **Termination demob reimbursement:** If Pemberton refuses AND concurrent orders <£500k/month → recommend walk\n3. **Benchmarking + MFC:** If Pemberton insists on unlimited benchmarking → price up 2–3%, becomes uncompetitive\n4. **Bid timing:** If no clarification window, submit redlines in bid response with clear rationale (don't wait for Pemberton to ask)\n\n## OPEN QUESTIONS FOR SPONSOR\n- What concurrent monthly order volume forecast do we have from Pemberton's supply chain?\n- What's our absolute minimum blended margin target (below which deal is accretive but not strategic)?\n- Can we commit £500k–£1m setup cost if termination demob is not recovered (insurance / contingency reserve)?\n- Is there appetite for a 2-year pilot framework if Pemberton won't commit to 3-year with volume floor?\n\n## RISK SUMMARY (IF NO REDLINES)\n- Margin compression risk: 37% (8% → 5% blended margin)\n- Termination cost (unrecovered): ~£300k–500k PV if exit year 1\n- Indemnity exposure: Uninsured, unlimited; single claim could exceed annual profit\n- **Verdict:** Bid is viable but risky; ROI drops from 25–30% to 12–18%. Redlines are worth pushing for.\n\n---\n\n**Next action:** Schedule sponsor call. Bring EXEC-SUMMARY + REDLINE-STRATEGY. Have insurance contact ready.\n**Timeline:** Bid due [DATE]; clarification window closes [DATE]. Act before window closes.\n"
